3. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The online game used in the study likely required software engineering expertise to develop and maintain, and the paper may discuss technical aspects of the game's design and implementation. 
4. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The study touches on issues related to online social behavior and the impact of technology on interpersonal relationships, which are relevant to the field of computers and society. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - While not directly related to the content of the paper, the study may involve computational complexity analysis of the algorithms used to analyze the linguistic data.
